      "message": "http: fix pool submission during shutdown race condition\n\nFixes a race where an http request attempts to submit a task to\nthe threadpool during server shutdown.\n\nThe race can be reproduced as follows:\n\n1) The server receives an http request.\n2) Processing of the request is delayed, and shutdown is triggered\n   in the meantime.\n3) During shutdown, the libevent callback is unregistered and the\n   threadpool interrupted.\n4) The delayed request (step 2) resumes and tries to submit a task\n   to the now-interrupted server.\n\nThis fix detects failed submissions immediately, and the server\nresponds with HTTP_SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE.",
